 Problembereich Mündlichkeit und Schriftlichkeit aufschlussreich sind, schließt die Untersuchung mit einem Plädoyer dafür, Konstruktionen als Phänomene alltäglicher kommunikativer Praxis zu begreifen.  aUsing the example of “nonfinite verbal construction” (“Me give up?”), this book tries to move from the everyday use of grammatical construction to its representation in linguistic usage knowledge. Some characteristics of “nonfinite verbal constructions” are discussed across languages and with a view to the problem area of speech and writing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aConstruction grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxVerb phrase. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxVerbals. 0aIndo-European languagesxVerb phrase. 4aGesprächsanalyse. 4aKognitive Grammatik. 4aPragmatik (Sprache). 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aPragmatics (linguistics).  acognitive grammar.  aconversation analysis.  asyntax.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311028260340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028271940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110282719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110282719/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014